  <h2>Next steps</h2>
  <p>
    Once you’re comfortable with Cursor and GitHub, you might:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Clone another project and run it locally.</li>
    <li>Make a small change (e.g. edit some text in this workshop) and, when you’re ready, learn how to commit and push.</li>
    <li>Use Cursor Chat to ask questions about code in your repo.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Add your own “getting started” links and next steps above by editing <code>src/pages/resources.astro</code>.
  </p>
